PN,38802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1781777898
OL,3,CLeisure firm fined #60,000 after
OL,4,Cfootballer fatally electrocuted by
OL,5,Cfloodlight
OL,7,FThe Health and Safety Executive found
OL,8,Fthat Parkwood Community Leisure
OL,9,FLimited had failed to inspect and
OL,10,Fmaintain worn and faulty wiring on the
OL,11,Ffloodlight.
OL,13,FA month before Albert's death - an off-
OL,14,Fduty police officer had suffered an
OL,15,Felectric shock from the same equipment.
OL,17,FAlong with the #60,000 fine, Parkwood
OL,18,Fmust also pay #40,000 in costs.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/4
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1781777898
OL,3,CLeisure firm fined #60,000 after
OL,4,Cfootballer fatally electrocuted by
OL,5,Cfloodlight
OL,7,FHSE inspector Dominic Goacher said:
OL,8,F"This tragic incident should never
OL,9,Fhave happened.
OL,11,F"What followed was a long and complex
OL,12,Finvestigation.
OL,14,F"We found that the electrical system
OL,15,Fof the floodlight that resulted in
OL,16,FAlbert's death had already been
OL,17,Fidentified by Parkwood as being in
OL,18,Fpoor condition, yet they failed to
OL,19,Ftake action to remedy the faults.
OL,26,@pD@AOUsD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/4
